OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,FCompetition for rental homes has
OL,7,Ffallen to its lowest level for the
OL,8,Fmonth of February in six years,
OL,9,Faccording to a property website.
OL,11,FZoopla said the average number of
OL,12,Finquiries per property was 4.8 in
OL,13,FFebruary, down from 6.5 last year,
OL,14,Fmeaning fewer renters typically
OL,15,Fcompeting for each home.
OL,17,FIt marks the lowest level in the month
OL,18,Fof February since February 2020, when
OL,19,Fthere were around 4.2 inquiries per
OL,20,Frental home.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,FZoopla said this was "clear evidence"
OL,7,Fof the rental market becoming more
OL,8,Fbalanced after a peak in competition
OL,9,Fseen in 2022 and 2023, with improved
OL,10,Fmortgage conditions having helped more
OL,11,Frenters to buy their first home.
OL,13,FUK rents for new lets increased by
OL,14,F1.9% over the year to January,
OL,15,Freaching #1,319 on average across the
OL,16,FUK the website said.
OL,26,@nD@VOUnD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,FThe report said: "Rental growth
OL,7,Fremains stronger in more affordable
OL,8,Fnorthern markets where rents are
OL,9,Flower. Cities such as Liverpool,
OL,10,FNewcastle and Glasgow are still
OL,11,Frecording stronger increases of 3% to
OL,12,F4.6%."
OL,14,FZoopla said it expected rents to
OL,15,Fincrease by around 2% to 3% on average
OL,16,Facross the UK during 2026.
OL,18,FIts rental market index is based on
OL,19,Fasking rents and adjusted to reflect
OL,20,Fachieved rents.
OL,26,@nD@ROUtD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,FRichard Donnell, executive director at
OL,7,FZoopla, said: "Market conditions for
OL,8,Frenters are the best they have been
OL,9,Ffor six years.
OL,11,F"The rental market is moving back
OL,12,Ftowards balance as demand cools and
OL,13,Fmore homes become available to rent.
OL,15,F"Renters are facing less competition
OL,16,Ffor homes and slower rent increases
OL,17,Fthan in recent years. Localised
OL,18,Fchanges in demand and supply are
OL,19,Fresulting in rents falling in some
OL,20,Fcities but this will be only a short-
OL,21,Flived trend.
OL,26,@oD@OOUsD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,F"However, supply remains well below
OL,7,Fpre-pandemic levels, which means
OL,8,Fincreasing the number of rental homes
OL,9,Fremains key to improving affordability
OL,10,Ffor the UK renters over the long-term."
OL,12,FTom Bill, head of UK residential
OL,13,Fresearch at Knight Frank, said: "More
OL,14,Fbalance has returned across the UK but
OL,15,Fin the capital, where renting is twice
OL,16,Fas common, there is still a notable
OL,17,Flack of supply in many areas that is
OL,18,Fpushing rents higher."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@gO]uD@aOUzD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,FMeanwhile, calculations from property
OL,7,Ffirm Savills indicated that the value
OL,8,Fof the UK's private rented sector fell
OL,9,Fby #48 billion in 2025, while the
OL,10,Fvalue of owner-occupied housing stock
OL,11,Fincreased by #185 billion.
OL,13,FThe value of the private rented sector
OL,14,Fhas shrunk for three years in a row,
OL,15,Faccording to Savills' calculations,
OL,16,Fwith the value of homes falling by a
OL,17,Ftotal of #79 billion since 2022, as
OL,18,Fincreased house prices have failed to
OL,19,Foffset the loss of stock.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,FLucian Cook, head of residential
OL,7,Fresearch at Savills, said: "Over the
OL,8,Fpast 25 years, we've grown accustomed
OL,9,Fto a story of the private rented
OL,10,Fsector expanding at the expense of
OL,11,Fpeople's ability to get onto the
OL,12,Fhousing ladder.
OL,14,F"But while deep-seated housing
OL,15,Fchallenges remain, lighter regulation
OL,16,Fin the mortgage market and tighter
OL,17,Foversight of the private rented sector
OL,18,Fare gradually beginning to shift that
OL,19,Fnarrative.
OL,26,@oD@\OUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,F"Changes in tenancy legislation,
OL,7,Fhigher operating costs and increased
OL,8,Fmortgage rates have prompted many
OL,9,Fprivate landlords to reassess their
OL,10,Fportfolios.
OL,12,F"Larger landlords, better equipped to
OL,13,Fabsorb added costs and requirements,
OL,14,Fhave taken on some of this stock,
OL,15,Fcontributing to a more
OL,16,Fprofessionalised PRS (private rented
OL,17,Fsector). But others have been sold to
OL,18,Fowner-occupiers, reducing the sector's
OL,19,Foverall size."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU{D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773209293
OL,3,CMarket conditions for renters 'best
OL,4,Cfor six years'
OL,6,FNathan Emerson, chief executive of
OL,7,Fproperty professionals' body
OL,8,FPropertymark, said: "We currently have
OL,9,Fa rental landscape where demand for
OL,10,Fproperties continues to outstrip
OL,11,Favailable stock.
OL,13,F"When looking at the latest data
OL,14,Favailable, Propertymark members report
OL,15,Fa near 7% increase in the number of
OL,16,Flandlords who have chosen to sell
OL,17,Ftheir properties year-on-year."
OL,26,@pD@UOUuD@AOUyD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
